This paper is likely to belong to the Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) sub-category as it deals with parsing formal languages and grammars. It may also belong to the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category as it proposes a new algorithm for parsing linear context-free rewriting systems. The paper may also be relevant to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category as it involves the use of matrix multiplication, which is a common technique in machine learning. The Computational Complexity (cs.CC) sub-category is also a possibility as the paper discusses the asymptotic complexity of parsing various formalisms. Finally, the Formal Languages and Automata Theory (cs.FL) sub-category may also be relevant as the paper deals with parsing formal languages and grammars.
